TITLE: Converting String Environment Variables to Numbers with t3-env
DESCRIPTION: Shows two methods to convert string environment variables to numbers: a manual approach using parseInt with validation, and a simpler approach using Zod's built-in coercion functionality.
SOURCE: https://github.com/t3-oss/t3-env/blob/main/docs/src/app/docs/recipes/page.mdx#2025-04-11_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export const env = createEnv({
  server: {
    SOME_NUMBER: z
      .string()
      // transform to number
      .transform((s) => parseInt(s, 10))
      // make sure transform worked
      .pipe(z.number()),

    // Alternatively, use Zod's default primitives coercion
    // https://zod.dev/?id=coercion-for-primitives
    ZOD_NUMBER_COERCION: z.coerce.number(),
  },
  // ...
});
```

